{NORTH has both Majors and planned on bidding 1\H first, (up-the-line). 
After WEST's overcall, NORTH makes a Negative Double, showing both Majors and at least 10 points to 
make a 2-level Negative Double.

SOUTH bids 2\H, showing a 4-card suit and minimum opening hand. Notice 
that this is not a Reverse by SOUTH, showing extra strength. She is not really bidding 
\Hs on her own, she is supporting partner's suit.

NORTH has 13 points so he bids 4\H.}

